window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Everyone thinks they know the real story behind the villains in fairy tales - but the villains themselves beg to differ. In <i>Troll's-Eye View</i>, you'll hear from the Giant's wife (\"Jack and the Beanstalk\"), Rumpelstiltskin, the oldest of the Twelve Dancing Princesses, and many more. A stellar lineup of authors, including Garth Nix, Jane Yolen, and Nancy Farmer, makes sure that these old stories do new tricks!</p> <p>Introduction copyright Ellen Datlow and Terri Windling, 2009; \"Wizard's Apprentice\" copyright Delia Sherman, 2009; \"An Unwelcome Guest\" copyright Garth Nix, 2009; \"Faery Tales\" copyright Wendy Froud, 2009; \"Rags and Riches\" copyright Nina Kiriki Hoffman, 2009; \"Up the Down Beanstalk: A Wife Remembers\" copyright Peter S. Beagle, 2009; \"The Shoes That Were Danced to Pieces\" copyright Ellen Kushner, 2009; \"Puss in Boots, the Sequel\" copyright Joseph Stanton, 2009; \"The Boy Who Cried Wolf \" copyright Holly Black, 2009; \"Troll\" copyright Jane Yolen, 2009; \"Castle Othello\" copyright Nancy Farmer, 2009; \"'Skin\" copyright Michael Cadnum, 2009; \"A Delicate Architecture\" copyright Catherynne M. Valente, 2009; \"Molly\" copyright Midori Snyder, 2009; \"Observing the Formalities\" copyright Neil Gaiman, 2009; \"The Cinderella Game\" copyright Kelly Link, 2009.</p>"; 
